# Project: Meal Menu Planner — Frontend
Application for creating meal menus over a specified time range.
Meals are selected automatically. Users can add their own products and recipes.
Users have accounts.

---

## Tech Stack
- Angular 21 (standalone components only — NO NgModules)
- NGXS (state management)
- TypeScript (strict)
- PrimeNG (UI components)
- Tailwind CSS (styling)

---

## Component Conventions
- ALL components must be standalone (`standalone: true`)
- ALL components must use `ChangeDetectionStrategy.OnPush`
- Use signals wherever possible (prefer `signal()`, `computed()`, `effect()` over traditional RxJS patterns when applicable)
- No inline styles — use Tailwind classes only
- Variables used in templates that are not inputs should be protected

## Styling
- Use TailwindCss for one line styling
- More than 3 styling properties should be moved to a separate class

## TypeScript
- Never use `any` — use `unknown` if a type cannot be determined
- Always type API responses through dedicated interfaces/models
- Prefer explicit types over inference where it improves readability
- Explicitly specify method visibility (public/private/protected)

## Naming
- Models: suffix `Model` (e.g. `RecipeModel`)
- DTOs: suffix `Dto` (e.g. `RecipeDto`)
- Files: `kebab-case.component.ts`, `kebab-case.service.ts`, etc.
- Boolean variables/properties: prefix and suffix depends on context (e.g. `isLoading`, `hasError`)

## File Structure
Top-level folders (inside `src/`):
- Each feature has its own folder at the root level (e.g. `account/` contains everything related to login, registration, password reset)
- `core/` — critical system-wide concerns only (e.g. error handling, navigation, auth guards)
- `shared/` — reusable, standalone pieces used across multiple features (single components, directives, pipes)

Inside each feature folder, split by type:
account/
  components/   ← views / UI components
  services/
  models/
  resolvers/
  ... (other types as needed)

- Do not put feature-specific code in `core/` or `shared/`
- Add to `shared/` only when a piece is genuinely reusable across features

## NGXS
- Actions in a dedicated file: `[feature].actions.ts`
- No HTTP calls in components — always go through services
- State selectors should be typed
- Use `@Selector()` decorator for selectors
- Use of Selector inside componets should be selectSignal()

---

## General Rules
- Do not introduce new patterns or libraries without explicit instruction
- When in doubt about style, look at existing code in the project and follow it
- Prefer simple, readable solutions over clever ones
- Do not leave TODO comments unless explicitly asked
